main event: A small bright white light was observed moving at a high rate of speed in the Pacific Ocean at 34-30N 174-30W.
interesting points: The light was estimated to be at an altitude of 30,000 to 50,000 feet.
The light traveled 30 arc miles in 2 minutes before fading at 2733Z.
The sighting lasted for 11 minutes and the characteristics of the object were not identifiable.
The report was submitted by the military and was part of Project Blue Book.
The report could not provide an evaluation of the sighting at the time.
